d [[Andrew Adams (American football)|Andrew Adams]])\n\n==Personal life==\n\nOn March 26, 2016, Talib married his girlfriend of over seven years, Gypsy Benitez, in a ceremony outside of [[Dallas, Texas]]. Teammates from the [[Denver Broncos]] and [[New England Patriots]] attended, although the Broncos defeated the Patriots in the AFC Championship less than three months prior.<ref>{{cite web| title=Aqib Talib got married and invited basically everyone in the NFL| url=https://www.ftw.usatoday.com/2016/03/aqib-talib-wedding-nfl-broncos-patriots-invited/amp| accessdate=February 5, 2018| website=ftw.usatoday.com| author=Charlotte Wilder| date=March 28, 2016| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160507014856/http://ftw.usatoday.com/2016/03/aqib-talib-wedding-nfl-broncos-patriots-invited/amp| archive-date=May 7, 2016| url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web| title=Broncos cornerback Aqib Talib ties the knot| url=https://www.247sports.com/nfl/denver-broncos/Bolt/Broncos-cornerback-Aqib-Talib-ties-the-knot-44513980/Amp| accessdate=February 5, 2018| website=247sports.com| author=Ian McCue| date=March 28, 2016}}</ref> The couple have two children together. His son is named Jabril and is the youngest, and his daughter is named Kiara, the oldest from a previous relationship in college.<ref>{{cite web| title=Aqib Talib's adorable daughter: 'We just made world history'| url=https://www.si.com/extra-mustard/2016/02/08/aqib-talib-broncos-daughter-press-conference-video-super-bowl| accessdate=February 5, 2018| website=si.com| date=February 8, 2016| author=Extra Mustard}}</ref>\n\nTalib has had several conduct related issues since his NFL career started. At the NFL rookie symposium in July 2008, Talib was involved in a fistfight with fellow Buccaneers rookie [[Cory Boyd]].<ref>[http://www.profootballtalk.com/2008/07/02/symposium-sluggers-identified/ ProFootballTalk.com \u2013 SYMPOSIUM SLUGGERS IDENTIFIED<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080703180116/http://www.profootballtalk.com/2008/07/02/symposium-sluggers-identified/ |date=July 3, 2008 }}</ref> In the early morning of June 5, 2016, Talib was shot in the leg outside a Dallas strip club. He was released from the hospital the same day.\n<ref>http://espn.go.com/nfl/story/_/id/15978684/denver-broncos-cb-aqib-talib-released-hospital-being-shot-leg</ref>\nIt was later revealed that Talib falsified the report, having actually shot himself in the leg and lied to police.\n<ref>http://www.espn.com/nfl/story/_/id/17716226/police-conclude-denver-broncos-aqib-talib-shot-leg</ref>\n\nTalib cites [[Michael Irvin]] and [[Deion Sanders]] as his favorite players as a child.<ref>{{cite web| title=Broncos' Aqib Talib opens up about rough childhood, path to NFL| url=https://247sports.com/nfl/denver-broncos/Bolt/Broncos-Aqib-Talib-opens-up-about-rough-childhood-path-to-NFL-40468988| accessdate=February 5, 2018| website=247sports.com| author=Ian McCue| date=October 22, 2015}}</ref>\n\n===Legal issues===\nOn August 20, 2009, Talib allegedly battered a taxi driver and he was arrested by [[Florida Highway Patrol]] and booked into the [[Pinellas County Sheriff's Office|Pinellas County jail]], charged with [[resisting arrest]] without violence and [[Battery (crime)|simple battery]].<ref>Pinellas county Sheriffs office [http://pcsoweb.com/InmateBooking/SubjectResults.aspx?id=1368098 PCSO]</ref><ref>{{cite web\n |title=Bucs' Talib charged with battery on cab driver \n |url=http://www2.tbo.com/content/2009/aug/20/201628/bucs-aqib-talib-charged-battery-resisting-arrest/sports-bucs/ \n |date=August 20, 2009\n | publisher=Tampa Bay Online \n |accessdate=August 20, 2009 \n |url-status=dead| archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090826145946/http://www2.tbo.com/content/2009/aug/20/201628/bucs-aqib-talib-charged-battery-resisting-arrest/sports-bucs/ \n |archivedate=August 26, 2009 \n}}</ref>\n\nIn March 2011, police in [[Garland, Texas]] issued a felony warrant for Talib for [[Aggravated assault|aggravated assault with a deadly weapon]] after he was accused of firing a gun at his sister's boyfriend.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://sports.espn.go.com/nfl/news/story?id=6270645 |title=Felony warrant issued for Tampa Bay Buccaneers cornerback Aqib Talib \u2013 ESPN |first=Pat |last=Yasinskas |publisher=ESPN |date=March 29, 2011 |accessdate=March 29, 2011}}</ref> He was later released on $25,000 bond. Talib was indicted on the charge in May 2011.<ref>{{cite news|agency = Associated Press|title=Bucs' Talib indicted in Dallas|url=http://msn.foxsports.com/nfl/story/Tampa-Bay-Buccaneers-Aqib-Talib-indicted-alleged-gun-charge-052711|accessdate=May 29, 2011|newspaper=[[USA Today]]|date=March 30, 2011}}</ref> On June 18, 2012, the charges were dropped due to insufficient evidence and character concerns with the accuser.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.tampabay.com/blogs/bucs/content/case-against-bucs-aqib-talib-was-dismissed |title=Case against Bucs' Aqib Talib was dismissed|accessdate=June 18, 2012|newspaper=[[Tampa Bay Times]]}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n[[No Fly Zone (Denver Broncos)|No Fly Zone]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category}}\n*{{NFL.com player}}\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20140312212102/http://www.denverbroncos.com/team/roster/Aqib-Talib/8b5aba78-4164-4bc6-a4cd-7b6c32dbb294 Denver Broncos bio]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20130304140610/http://www.patriots.com/team/roster/Aqib-Talib/7e3ac420-1de6-476e-b240-e00e4bfd1e0a New England Patriots bio]\n* [http://www.nfldraftscout.com/ratings/dsprofile.php?pyid=12274&draftyear=2008&genpos=CB NFL Draft Scout profile]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20071013074620/http://kuathletics.cstv.com/sports/m-footbl/mtt/talib_aqib00.html Kansas Jayhawks bio]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20101212004139/http://www.buccaneers.com/team/roster/Aqib-Talib/0d52c9b4-6a04-4bab-bd84-bfade794f6d5 Tampa Bay Buccaneers bio]\n\n{{Miami Dolphins roster navbox}}\n{{Navboxes\n|