{"title_page": "Ek Mutthi Aasmaan (TV series)", "text_new": "{{short description|Indian television series}}\n{{About|the television series|the 1973 Bollywood film|Ek Mutthi Aasmaan}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=May 2015}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2015}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name      = Ek Mutthi Aasmaan \n| genre          = [[Drama]]\n| runtime        = 25 Minutes  \n| camera         = [[Multi camera]]\n| creator        = [[DJ's a Creative Unit]]\n| writer         =  Satyam Tripathi <br>  Shilpa Choubay <br> Sushil Choubay <br>[[Dheeraj Sarna]]<br> Damini Kanwal Shetty \n| editor         = [[Santosh Singh]] <br> Pradeep Singh\n| director       = Hemant Prabhu <br> [[Abhimanyu Chauhan]]\n| country        = [[India]]\n| language       = [[Hindi]]\n| num_episodes   =<!--figure has been contested. do not add without providing a reliably published source.-->\n| starring       = [[Rachana Parulkar]]/[[Asha Negi]] as Kalpana <br> [[Ashish Chaudhary]] as Raghav <br> [[Shilpa Shirodkar]] as Kamla <br> Shireena Sambyal as Pakhi\n| channel        = [[Zee TV]]\n| location       = [[Mumbai]]\n| company        = [[DJ's a Creative Unit]]\n| producer       = [[Tony Singh (director)|Tony Singh]] <br> Deeya Singh\n| picture_format = [[576i]] ([[SDTV]]) <br> [[1080i]] ([[HDTV]])\n| num_seasons    = 1\n| first_aired    = {{start date|2013|08|26}}\n| last_aired     = {{end date|2014|09|12}}\n| website        = http://www.zeetv.com/shows/ek-muthi-asmaan/\n}}\n\n'''''Ek Mutthi Aasmaan''''' (English Title: ''[[Reach For The Stars (Indian TV series)|Reach For The Stars]])'' was an [[India]]n family drama [[television]] show. Neha Pandey was in charge of casting<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/hindi/Neha-Pandey-Simplicity-was-my-brief-for-casting-actors-inthis-movie/articleshow/48514847.cms|title=Neha Pandey simplicity was my brief for casting actors|work=www.timesofindia.indiatimes.com|author=TOI}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-12-06/news/44862762_1_tv-soap-tv-show-tv-actors|title=Actor returns to television after delivering a Bollywood hit|work=[[The Times of India]]|accessdate=26 November 2015}}</ref> It aired on [[Zee TV]] from Monday to Friday in the evening.\n\nThe show was dubbed in English and aired on [[Zee World]], [[DStv|DSTV]] and dubbed in [[Tamil language|Tamil]] as ''En Kanmani'' (My Lovely) on [[Polimer TV]]. It is currently still available in the original Hindi version for the audience on [[ZEE5]].<ref>{{cite news|title=EK Mutthi Aasmaan|url=https://www.zee5.com/tvshows/details/ek-mutthi-aasmaan/0-6-439|publisher=Zee5|access-date=20 March 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Plot summary==\n\n''Ek Mutthi Aasmaan'' follows the story of Kalpana \"Kalpi\" Jadhav ([[Rachana Parulkar]]) and Raghav Singhania ([[Ashish Chaudhary]]), as their paths cross on a journey of self improvement. Kalpi is the daughter of a maid, Kamla Jadhav ([[Shilpa Shirodkar]]), and a mill worker, Vitthal Jadhav (Mohit Dagga). Her mother's dream is to become a part of the middle class so she works tirelessly. Kalpana selflessly loves her mother, but is deprived of her love and attention because Kamla is always busy looking after family members of her employers, mostly Pakhi Kapoor (Shirina Singh).\n\nRaghav Singhania is a rich businessman whose mission is to take revenge from the Kapoors who murdered his father. Raghav has always been in debt to Kamla as she helped him escape from the Kapoors who wanted to adopt him and take away all his wealth. He becomes attracted to Kalpi's sweet, simple and caring nature and falls in love with her. Eventually, Kalpana recognizes Raghav's feelings and reciprocates. Raghav and Kalpana fall in love, and with the blessing of their parents, plan their wedding.\n\nOn the day of his wedding to Kalpi, Raghav marries Pakhi Kapoor instead. Eventually, Raghav realizes his mistake but cannot rectify it because his mother, Gauri, wants him to use his marriage to Pakhi in her plans against the Kapoors. In order to prove his love for Kalpi, he marries her by putting the ''[[sindoor]]'' on her forehead in a temple.\n\nPaakhi hires goons to kidnap Kalpi and keep her in a remote location. Later, Raghav learns where Paakhi is hiding Kalpi and rescues her. A car chase ensues in which the car drives off a cliff and blows up. Some fishermen find Kalpi in the river and take her to a hospital; Raghav is still missing. While in the hospital, Dhiraj Diwan is depressed over his niece Suhana's ([[Asha Negi]]) death. When he hears how Kalpi's face has been burned and that she has lost her memory, he requests the doctor to perform a plastic surgery procedure to make Kalpi look like Suhana. The surgery is successful. Suhana has flashbacks of her real family, the accident and struggles to believe she is indeed Suhana Diwan.\n\nOn the day Suhana is to marry Aryan (Kunal Varma), she realizes that she is Kalpi and she marries Raghav instead. \n<!--As an Encyclopedia, Wikipedia provides a plot SUMMARY not a recreation of every plot twist. This summary has reached the recommended MAXIMUM LENGTH. Any additional details added without condensing or removing less important details will be subject to IMMEDIATE REMOVAL.-->\n\n==Cast==\n\n* [[Rachana Parulkar|Rachna Parulkar]] / [[Asha Negi]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/hindi/Asha-Negi-enters-Ek-Mutthi-Aasman/articleshow/39409337.cms|title=Asha Negi enters Ek Mutthi Aasman - Times of India|website=The Times of India|language=en|access-date=2019-07-27}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bollywoodlife.com/news-gossip/ek-mutthi-aasmaan-asha-negi-bags-the-new-lead-role-377751/|title=Ek Mutthi Aasmaan: Asha Negi bags the new lead role {{!}} Bollywood Life|date=2014-07-24|website=www.bollywoodlife.com|language=en-EN|access-date=2019-07-27}}</ref> as Kalpana Raghav Singhania \"Kalpi\", Raghav's wife and childhood friend \n** [[Mehnaaz Maan]] as young Kalpi\n* [[Ashish Chaudhary]] as Raghav Singhania, Kalpana's husband and childhood friend<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-a-chopper-entry-for-ashish-chowdhry-1928153|title=A chopper entry for Ashish Chowdhry|work=[[Daily News and Analysis]]|accessdate=26 November 2015}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/ashish-chowdhry-gets-bollywood-offers-as-he-gears-up-for-a-tv-show/417372-44.html|title=News18.com: CNN-News18 Breaking News India, Latest News Headlines, Live News Updates|website=News18|language=en-US|access-date=2019-07-27}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.filmibeat.com/television/news/2013/ek-mutthi-aasman-brings-ashish-chowdhry-back-tv-118007.html|title=Ek Mutthi Aasman Brings Ashish Chowdhry Back To TV|date=2013-08-23|website=Filmibeat|language=en|access-date=2019-07-27}}</ref>\n** Yatin Mehta as young Raghav\n* [[Shilpa Shirodkar|Shilpa Shirodhkar]] as Kamla Vitthal Jadhav, Kalpi's mother<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://archive.indianexpress.com/news/ek-muthi-aasman-is-new-beginning-for-me-shilpa-shirodkar/1148665|title=Ek Muthi Aasman is new beginning for me: Shilpa Shirodkar - Indian Express|website=archive.indianexpress.com|access-date=2019-07-27}}</ref>\n* Mohit Dagga as Vitthal Jadhav, Kalpi's father<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.tellychakkar.com/tv/tv-news/whoever-sees-my-emotional-scenes-ek-mutthi-aasmaan-will-never-neglect-me-actor-mohit|title=Whoever sees my emotional scenes in Ek Mutthi Aasmaan will never neglect me as an actor \u2013 Mohit Dagga|last=Team|first=Tellychakkar|website=Tellychakkar.com|language=en|access-date=2019-07-27}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://zeeworldmovies.com/reach-for-the-stars/happy-birthday-to-mohit-dagga-popuarly-known-as-vitthal-jadhav/|title=Happy birthday to Mohit Dagga popuarly known as \"Vitthal Jadhav\"|date=2017-08-12|website=ZEE WORLD INTERNATIONAL|language=en-GB|access-date=2019-07-27}}</ref>\n* Shirina Sambyal as Pakhi Kapoor<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bollywoodlife.com/news-gossip/shirina-inspired-from-urmila-matondkar-for-tv-role-369412/|title=Shirina inspired from Urmila Matondkar for TV role {{!}} Bollywood Life|date=2014-07-07|website=www.bollywoodlife.com|language=en-EN|access-date=2019-07-27}}</ref>\n** [[Avneet Kaur]] as young Pakhi<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/hindi/Avneet-Kaur-Jasmine-Avasia-in-Ek-Mutthi-Aasman/articleshow/21934076.cms|title=Avneet Kaur & Jasmine Avasia in Ek Mutthi Aasman - Times of India|website=The Times of India|language=en|access-date=2019-07-27}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/brunch/the-little-telly-star/story-0dLkwG4RC05aYWRJ7S1TXN.html|title=The little telly star|date=2013-08-25|website=Hindustan Times|language=en|access-date=2019-07-27}}</ref>\n* [[Ashish Nayyar]] as Sahil Kapoor, Pakhi's father\n* Tuhina Vohra as Neetu Kapoor, Pakhi's mother\n* [[Jyoti Gauba]] as Gauri Singhania, Raghav's mother<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/hindi/Jyoti-Gauba-in-Ek-Muthhi-Aasmaan/articleshow/31960705.cms|title=Jyoti Gauba in Ek Muthhi Aasmaan - Times of India|website=The Times of India|language=en|access-date=2019-07-27}}</ref>\n* Siddhant Agarwal as Pakhya Jadhav, Kalpi's brother\n* [[Suman Shashi Kant]] as Manda Tai\n* [[Neeraj Malviya]] as Prem Kapoor, Pakhi's brother<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/hindi/Zee-TV-Neeraj-Malviya-Ek-Mutthi-Aasmaan-Ek-Hazaaron-Mein-Meri-Behna-Hai/articleshow/26208138.cms|title=Neeraj Malviya to enter Ek Mutthi Aasmaan? - Times of India|website=The Times of India|language=en|access-date=2019-07-27}}</ref>\n* [[Jasmine Avasia]] as Rajji Kapoor<ref name=\":0\" />\n* [[Ishaan Singh Manhas|Ishaan Singh Manhaas]] as Samar \"Sammy\" Raizada, Raghav's friend and business partner \n* [[Asha Negi]] as Suhana Diwan\n* Siraj Mustafa as Dhiraj Dhawan, Suhana's brother\n* [[Shweta Gautam]] as Kavita Diwan\n* [[Rohit Sagar]] as Sanjay Diwan\n* [[Kunal Verma]] as Aryan, Suhana's love interest<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/hindi/Kunal-Verma-is-Aasha-Negis-new-love-in-Ek-Mutthi-Aasman/articleshow/40052927.cms|title=Kunal Verma is Aasha Negi\u2019s new love in Ek Mutthi Aasman - Times of India|website=The Times of India|language=en|access-date=2019-07-27}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n== External links ==\n*{{Official website|http://www.zeetv.com/shows/ek-muthi-asmaan}}\n\n{{Zee TV Programmes}}\n\n[[Category:Indian television soap operas]]\n[[Category:Zee TV television series]]\n[[Category:Hindi-language television programs]]\n[[Category:Indian drama television series]]\n[[Category:2013 Indian television series debuts]]\n[[Category:2014 Indian television series endings]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Indian television series}}\n{{About|the television series|the 1973 Bollywood film|Ek Mutthi Aasmaan}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=May 2015}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2015}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name      = Ek Mutthi Aasmaan \n| genre          = [[Drama]]\n| runtime        = 25 Minutes  \n| camera         = [[Multi camera]]\n| creator        = [[DJ's a Creative Unit]]\n| writer         =  Satyam Tripathi <br>  Shilpa Choubay <br> Sushil Choubay <br>[[Dheeraj Sarna]]<br> Damini Kanwal Shetty \n| editor         = [[Santosh Singh]] <br> Pradeep Singh\n| director       = Hemant Prabhu <br> [[Abhimanyu Chauhan]]\n| country        = [[India]]\n| language       = [[Hindi]]\n| num_episodes   =<!--figure has been contested. do not add without providing a reliably published source.-->\n| starring       = [[Rachana Parulkar]]/[[Asha Negi]] as Kalpana <br> [[Ashish Chaudhary]] as Raghav <br> [[Shilpa Shirodkar]] as Kamla <br> Shireena Sambyal as Pakhi\n| channel        = [[Zee TV]]\n| location       = [[Mumbai]]\n| company        = [[DJ's a Creative Unit]]\n| producer       = [[Tony Singh (director)|Tony Singh]] <br> Deeya Singh\n| picture_format = [[576i]] ([[SDTV]]) <br> [[1080i]] ([[HDTV]])\n| num_seasons    = 1\n| first_aired    = {{start date|2013|08|26}}\n| last_aired     = {{end date|2014|09|12}}\n| website        = http://www.zeetv.com/shows/ek-muthi-asmaan/\n}}\n\n'''''Ek Mutthi Aasmaan''''' (English Title: ''[[Reach For The Stars (Indian TV series)|Reach For The Stars]])'' was an [[India]]n family drama [[television]] show. Neha Pandey was in charge of casting<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/hindi/Neha-Pandey-Simplicity-was-my-brief-for-casting-actors-inthis-movie/articleshow/48514847.cms|title=Neha Pandey simplicity was my brief for casting actors|work=www.timesofindia.indiatimes.com|author=TOI}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-12-06/news/44862762_1_tv-soap-tv-show-tv-actors|title=Actor returns to television after delivering a Bollywood hit|work=[[The Times of India]]|accessdate=26 November 2015}}</ref> It aired on [[Zee TV]] from Monday to Friday in the evening.\n\nThe show was dubbed in English and aired on [[Zee World]], [[DStv|DSTV]] and dubbed in [[Tamil language|Tamil]] as ''En Kanmani'' (My Lovely) on [[Polimer TV]]. It is currently still available in the original Hindi version for the audience on [[ZEE5]].<ref>{{cite news|title=EK Mutthi Aasmaan|url=https://www.zee5.com/tvshows/details/ek-mutthi-aasmaan/0-6-439|publisher=Zee5|access-date=20 March 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Plot summary==\n\n''Ek Mutthi Aasmaan'' follows the story of Kalpana \"Kalpi\" Jadhav ([[Rachana Parulkar]]) and Raghav Singhania ([[Ashish Chaudhary]]), as their paths cross on a journey of self improvement. Kalpi is the daughter of a maid, Kamla Jadhav ([[Shilpa Shirodkar]]), and a mill worker, Vitthal Jadhav (Mohit Dagga). Her mother's dream is to become a part of the middle class so she works tirelessly. Kalpana selflessly loves her mother, but is deprived of her love and attention because Kamla is always busy looking after family members of her employers, mostly Pakhi Kapoor (Shirina Singh).\n\nRaghav Singhania is a rich businessman whose mission is to take revenge from the Kapoors who murdered his father. Raghav has always been in debt to Kamla as she helped him escape from the Kapoors who wanted to adopt him and take away all his wealth. He becomes attracted to Kalpi's sweet, simple and caring nature and falls in love with her. Eventually, Kalpana recognizes Raghav's feelings and reciprocates. Raghav and Kalpana fall in love, and with the blessing of their parents, plan their wedding.\n\nOn the day of his wedding to Kalpi, Raghav gets married to Pakhi Kapoor instead. Eventually, Raghav realizes his mistake but cannot rectify it because his mother, Gauri, wants him to use his marriage to Pakhi in her plans against the Kapoors. In order to prove his love for Kalpi, he gets married to her by putting the ''[[sindoor]]'' on her forehead in a temple.\n\nPaakhi hires goons to kidnap Kalpi and keep her in a remote location. Later, Raghav learns where Paakhi is hiding Kalpi and rescues her. A car chase ensues in which the car drives off a cliff and blows up. Some fishermen find Kalpi in the river and take her to a hospital; Raghav is still missing. While in the hospital, Dhiraj Diwan is depressed over his niece Suhana's ([[Asha Negi]]) death. When he hears how Kalpi's face has been burned and that she has lost her memory, he requests the doctor to perform a plastic surgery procedure to make Kalpi look like Suhana. The surgery is successful. Suhana gets flashbacks of her real family, the accident and struggles to believe she is indeed Suhana Diwan.\n\nOn the day Suhana is to marry Aryan (Kunal Varma), she realizes that she is Kalpi and she gets married to Raghav instead. \n<!--As an Encyclopedia, Wikipedia provides a plot SUMMARY not a recreation of every plot twist. This summary has reached the recommended MAXIMUM LENGTH. Any additional details added without condensing or removing less important details will be subject to IMMEDIATE REMOVAL.-->\n\n==Cast==\n\n* [[Rachana Parulkar